key_points: Travel blogger Jenn Bethune identified Gabby Petito's van in her video footage and informed the FBI.
Bethune's footage was captured during her trip to Grand Teton National Park.
ABC's '20/20' episode titled 'Life on Line: The Last Days of Gabby Petito' features Bethune's story among others.
The episode explores Gabby Petito and Brian Laundrie's last days, including the discovery of Laundrie's remains.
Interviews with former Moab police chief, experts on body language, and legal analysts are included to analyze police body cam footage.
Gabby Petito was on a cross-country road trip with her fiancé Brian Laundrie when she disappeared.
Other interviews featured in the episode include Miranda Baker who encountered Laundrie, and Jason Jensen, a private investigator.
Mykel Hawke, a retired special forces veteran, guides through the Carlton Reserve where Laundrie's body was found.
The program calls attention to missing persons of color and indigenous women in the same area as Petito.
'Life on Line: The Last Days of Gabby Petito' is streaming on Hulu.
spokespersons: Jim Winder (Former Moab, Utah, Police Chief)
Jason Jensen (Private Investigator and co-founder of the Cold Case Coalition)
Mykel Hawke (Retired Special Forces Combat Veteran and Survival Expert)
